Subject: [PATCH 0/2] media: synopsys: hdmirx: add HDMI RX audio capture

This series adds audio capture support to the Synopsys DesignWare HDMI RX
controller driver (RK3588). The mainline driver currently handles video
only; the hardware also delivers the audio embedded in the incoming HDMI
stream, which this series exposes as an ALSA capture device.

The controller feeds the recovered audio to an on-SoC I2S controller. The
driver registers the generic hdmi-codec as a child so a simple-audio-card
in the device tree can bind the HDMI RX audio DAI
(cpu = <&i2sN>, codec = <&hdmirx 0>).

The audio sample rate is derived from the ACR N/CTS values and the
measured TMDS character rate. A periodic worker keeps the local audio
reference clock locked to the source by adjusting it in small ppm steps
to hold the audio FIFO fill level near its target, avoiding FIFO
under/overflow and dropped samples.

Tested on an Orange Pi 5 Plus (RK3588) capturing 44.1/48 kHz stereo from
a phone over HDMI; playback is clean with no dropped samples.

